Who doesn't love this store. I go out of my way to go there because it's an easy in and out and I only buy my meat here because it's fresh and the quality is excellent. The produce is beautiful. < text>

1568012684264<//date>
< rate>
1</rate>
<review>The administrator was the reason for most of the lack of care. My friend was there for one year and it went from fair to  horrible in a short time.
First the good stuff, the front desk ladies, maintenance men and a few caregivers were wonderful and kind.
My friend would ring for help and it might arrive in 30min or not at all. I would get a phone call from him for help. I was told by the Administrator that there was two night caregivers giving out meds. Not true, the night med lady told me she was the only one.
He fell many times and was sent to the VA or Cedars many times.
When the property got sold, it really went to hell. The person who managed the med room was one of the best they had and he left. There was another med manager who left after four weeks.

<text>I met with, toured, spoke at length with, and even called and spoke to client/family references regarding CityView for the care of my mother. I encourage you to do so and to read the data for "City View" on the CA Dept. of Social Services website.  It is listed under two words with their address on La Brea and matching License #.   There are NO citations.  NO complaints.  Do not mistake them for other City Views in other cities.  In no way did I find this assisted living/memory care facility to be anything but the excellent home with a superior caring staff so predominately spoken of.

The Executive Director, Murielle Chocron, was kind, professional, and did not have an "air about her" as some other reviewer stated.   It is obvious that Murielle is very intelligent, educated, and knows what she is doing plus she is very compassionate and sincere.   I don't know about you but that is the kind of director I want to see where my mother lives.  I've now seen and toured over a dozen facilities and my mother has lived at several. My mother needed help with her medications and also some help bathing witch was provided. Assistance was provided as much as was required so as to keep my mom as mobile as possible. <user>111655966593220974474<//user><user_name>Murray Aronson< /user_name>< Date>
1566103477873</Date>
<Rate>4< /Rate>< Review>
I was part of a birthday celebration.  The food was good and plentiful.  Someone else who ordered the tempura that the breading was too heavy.  I agree, but I wouldn't order tempura in a Thai restaurant.  For one thing I wound not call that dish tempura, I'd call it Thai fried shrimp with vegetables.   We had beef with string beans, Angel duck,.braised sole filet, a noodle dish not pad thai, lemon chicken, and of course rice, including a sweet coconut rice which would have better as a dessert dish.  We also had a flavorful soup and spring rolls.  The service was good and efficient.  I found the decor of this small restaurant quite charming.  It's located in a mini-mall on Wilshire Blvd near midtown San Vicente with adequate parking.</Review>

I absolutely love this place! Thai food is one of my favorite foods and this place really stands out when it comes to selecting a Thai restaurant to dine in. In town on a fishing trip. Came to Copper Top on a recommendation and I'm so glad we did. Oh My God this place is the real deal. The smell of smoke in the air before we even pulled up. The food looked and smelled great but when it got to my table it blew us away. Some of the best ribs I've ever had in my life. They didn't need it at all but the spicy bbq sauce I put on them was a welcome addition. The tri tip was perfectly cooked. So tender and juicy. And the Mac & cheese... Incredible doesn't begin to describe it. The pit masters were the nicest guys ever and even took our picture for us. We will definitely be back again and again</Review>

< text>
Delicious barbecue made by father and son team Hank and Matthew. The meats are cooked in huge smokers out front, easy to see from the 395 through Big Pine. They have a variety of meats, but mine and my boyfriend‚Äôs favorite is the Saint Louis style pork ribs. Perfectly tender and falling off the bone, juicy and seasoned to enhance the flavor of the meat itself.
There‚Äôs a beautiful outdoor seating area with wide views of the Sierra as you enjoy your barbecue, and a heated room for the cold days.
Also, there‚Äôs a barbecue vending machine.<//text>

< review>
The first stop on our road trip and let me tell you.. It was so worth it!!! Lets start with the people. The second you walk up they are greeting you with a huge smile and a welcoming attitude. I asked if I could do the online ordering, but because they are so dang good they got slammed online and for the moment had paused the online orders. Makes sense to cater to those that are there in person.  They had the covid floor markers for social distancing and everyone wore a mask which I appreciated along with sealed plasticware.  The food came in its own sealed plastic container that kept it warm enough while we drove down the road to a nice little campground where we enjoyed the best BBQ ever. We had the 2 person plate which included ribs, tri tip, pulled pork, and your choice of sides. We had the mac and cheese and potato salad. Those sides were some of the best I have ever had, but the highlight were the ribs. Do not skip out on the ribs!!! For most of our road trip we wouldn't stop talking about that BBQ spot and on our way back we stopped by to take some pics of their new upcoming location down the block. So we knew exactly where to go the next time around.  Thanks Copper Top for the great tasting BBQ.< /review>

<userid>107706900704704682627<//userid>< Review>
I don't like barbecue food, but the ribs here are amazing! The barbecue sauce is served on the side, so it doesn't come  with it dripping all over so you can actually taste the meat and seasonings.

There is a dirt parking lot at the back of the restaurant, but if you have an RV, you can park along Locust and walk over to the restaurant.

Casual seating at outside tables with umbrellas or in a barn like steel building housing picnic tables with a view of the Eastern Sierra.

Definitely recommended!<//Review>

<response>None< /response><Rating>5< /Rating><name>Alyissia Gleason</name><date>1611079475896< /date><Text>First time to this place and I have to say I really enjoyed it. I got the pulled pork sandwhich with potato salad and Mac n cheese with a brownie and a bottled rootbeer. While my boyfriend had 1/2lb smoked tri tip.

My sandwhich was served on a pretzel bun lightly toasted. It is a good size serving with lots of flavor. Potato salad was a tad to pickle-y for me but if you like pickles go for it. The brownie was super delicious thick and cold and  palm size definitely worth the price. Now we get to the root beer....its not A&W or Barts it is its own taste. To me it tastes like a root beer popsicle you had on hot summer days in the 90's. Or those root beer candies your grandma always had.

As for the tri tip it was just the right amount of smoke juicy and tender. It had the right amount of char on the outside.

All in all it was a wonderful place to eat friendly and knowledgeable staff. We will be returning. Thank you so much for the enjoyable experience Copperas Top!<//Text><UserId.>111101470188601058718</UserId.></record></dataset><record>

109516872923861892273< /user>
<name>Ethan Dang</name><Date>1560300616098</Date><Rating>5</Rating>< Text>
This is my first trip to Mammoth mountain and my friends recommended me to stop by Copper Top BBQ on the way back. Best recommendation ever! The staff is extremely polite, passionate, and friendly. The place is kept clean and tidy (shoutouts to everyone that cleans up after themselves! i cant imagine putting my hands on someone elses leftover barbeque sauce...). I was able to try the ribs and tri tip (Tri tip meal with pickle and extra buns in the picture), and man... was it delicious. I'm not very good at explaining the taste, but if you enjoy barbeque, this is a place to stop by after or before a day of enjoying the slopes.

And thankyou to Copper Top for being environmentally aware with the use of compostable plastics!!</Text>

<Name>Logan Datin< /Name><date>1567702009855</date><Rate>5</Rate>< review>
This is a phenomenal BBQ joint. It has outdoor seating, long lines, and delicious food. There is a reason the line took 40 minutes, and I do not regret waiting. After I was done with the sampler plate, I decided the ribs were the best, and instead of waiting in line again to order some more, I went to their vending machine and bought a half rack of ribs for 17 bucks. The vending machine items are fresh, but they vacuum seal them so that you heat them up later. I brought them to my parents as a gift and they agreed that the ribs were amazing. <userid>102153220420411626109< /userid>< Name>
Amy Lloyd< /Name>
<Time>1559243509510<//Time><Rate>5< /Rate>< text>
I am not the biggest fan of BBQ but Copper Top was so good that I'm determined to make it a tradition to eat here every time I do a trip to Mammoth! Definitely not going to contest the "#1 in the USA" signage out front!

We made sure to get here before it opened and there was already a line. When you drive by you can see the smoke coming out from the copper top grills and you just get hungry from the sight.

As first timers, the bf and I ordered the Big Pine Sampler to get a taste of multiple things, and a side of Fire Roasted Green Chilies with Beans, dinner rolls, and of course pickle! The sampler plate included ribs, pulled pork, and tri tip. The ribs were unanimously the favorite in our group. While it was not fall-off-the-bone tender, the ribs were so flavorful and so smokey that I didn't even use any BBQ sauce that they gave us on the side. Besides, the meat texture was perfect with right amount of bite to it.

Seating may be hard to come by if you arrive late, but nothing wrong with eating outside while looking at picturesque mountains in the distance. The workers here are also all very friendly so the whole time it was very pleasant to eat here. I will definitely be back again!< /text>
<Pictures>None</Pictures><Resp>{'time': 1565312250670, 'text': 'Wow Amy, that was an amazing review to read, we are very humbled by your praise. We so look forward to seeing you again next time you can make it to our neck of the woods.'}<//Resp>< GmapID>

Jesse Thien< /user_name>
<Date>1533346813242</Date><Rating>5<//Rating>< review>
We have passed by this place many times and always said we needed to give it a try. Today was that day and we were not let down. The service was quick and friendly enough. There wasn't a ton of seating, but they did what they could with the space they have, and there was lots of provided shade. The flies are everywhere, but it is unavoidable, so just be aware. And finally, the food. We ordered the two sandwich options and a side of the fire roasted green chile with beans. The meat was cooked tender enough, was not dripping in sauce, and the flavor was    balanced without being overwhelming in any one aspect.  The bread completed the experience, able to hold up to the hefty sandwich without falling apart while delivering a mildly sweet taste.  My wife says it was the best bbq she's had. I almost agree with her. But we both agree that this will be a new must-stop when we pass through.   Well done, Copper Top.</review>

< Name>
Anthony Ross<//Name>
<Gmap_id>0x80be49e5a0a9d64b:0xb4d2795461a540fa< /Gmap_id>< Review>
I've been to some of the best Barbecue spots in the country. I've been through Texas, Missouri, North Carolina and Georgia and it pleases me to say that another BBQ giant is currently in the making. I can confidently that Hank at Copper Top is quite possibly one of the best Pit Masters I have ever met. This location doesn't have a large parking lot or a massive inside dining area, instead you park on the street and you walk up to a small hut and order. If you dont know what you want, you can walk over to the pit and actually look and see what Hank is making. It is unfortunate that this location is so far from anywhere that I frequently visit but the solution to that is that Copper Top will ship out your order! This is hands down, the best Barbecue in California. If you drive through Big Pine, take a visit to Copper Top and try the Ribs, you will not be disappointed.<//Review>

{'time': 1555109176166, 'text': "Hey there, many customers get this confused and I will attempt to clear it up for you. Our chicken is heavily smoked, which ends up turning many parts of the chicken PINK. A few customers a day ask us this and we have to explain (even show them by putting it back on the BBQ just to have it turn out MORE PINK) the smoking process. Just like smoked turkey at a fair, an example can be seen here: http://www.bemindfulbehuman.com/index.php/thanksgiving-prep-week-2016-turkey-leg-quarters-two-ways-smoked-and-roasted/\nThe pictures in this article show exactly what I'm talking about. While it's not impossible that we made a mistake during cooking, to this date, every customer that has brought me their chicken and asked me to cook it more was merely mistaking smoked meat for raw meat. We take our chicken cooking very seriously and use a penetration probe thermometer on each one, which is why I highly doubt you got raw chicken. I hope with this new information in mind, you will be willing come back and visit us again. Thank you for your time informing us of your concern!\n\nMatthew Kerley-Otten, Co-Owner"}</resp>

< text>
Highly recommend to anyone that appreciates tasty BBQ! Copper Top BBQ easily has the best BBQ in The Sierras. We've made it our regular pit stop on LA to Tahoe trips.

Father (Hank) is usually out front manning the smoker and grills while son (Matthew) is inside interfacing with customers.

They use the right amount of seasoning and cook to perfect level of pink in middle.

Make sure to order both the ribs and tri-tip.</text>

<userid>106494476795934714994</userid><user_name>Andres Rustan<//user_name><time>1473901726736</time><Rate>5< /Rate>< review>
am so glad we decided to return home passing by Big Pine. We were already heading back home and had no plans to stop for lunch, but we drove by Copper Top and the amazing smell made us turn around and stop there for lunch. Little we knew that this was voted the best BBQ in the country.... and it's true!!!

This is the best BBQ I have in a long time and probably the best ever. I was born in Argentina, so I've seen good bbq in my life. My wife is from Spain and she barely eats meat, but she had to have some chicken and taste the ribs and pulled pork I order. We don't eat meat at home and only have it once in a while when we know it's from a good source. This was the perfect time and the most amazing and tasty meal.

The staff is friendly and service is great and speedy. Hank, the owner, is constantly taking care of the grill and chatting with people. This is an amazing man with a true passion for what he does. The bbq grills are right by the tables and you can smell the wood burning while you wait and during the meal. It's a great experience. I am photographer, so I couldn't resist doing a few shots of Hank working the grills. I am planning to make a stop at Copper Top every time I am anywhere near the area.

I have a new friend in Big Pine now.  ;-)      Thanks!!!<//review>

<review>When my dad mentioned this awesome BBQ place in Big Pine I was thrilled to give it a try. Upon driving up I read the signs claiming that they were ranked the #1 in restaurant in the U.S. and I became skeptical saying things like ‚Äúoh yeah, according to who?‚Äù. Nonetheless, I was excited to try the food after getting hit with that wonderful BBQ aroma while walking past the giant copper topped smoker and up to the menu. My wife and I each ordered the tri-tip sandwiches with a side of potato salad and coleslaw. I think it was the best tri-tip I have ever had‚Ä¶ and the pretzel-like sandwich buns added to the flavor. The side dishes were equally as good! There is a good amount of outdoor seating and even an enclosed shed seating area. Everyone working there was very kind and you can tell that they love what they do. I was impressed‚Ä¶ so impressed that I looked into this #1 ranking claim and sure enough, there it was. Copper Top BBQ was ranked #1 on Yelps list of top restaurants for 2015... Need I say more?<//review><pics>None<//pics><Response>{'time': 1482970283124, 'text': "The best tri-tip you've ever had, Bryan? Now that's a true compliment, and I don't take it lightly. {'time': 1533158858192, 'text': "Hey there Marissa,\n\nI apologize that your visit was not up to our normal standards that most people enjoy at our place. I am saddened to see this review and will look into it. If the food was cold, I think I know what may have happened. I was training a new employee at the table around the time of this review and one of the things he was having an issue with was making sure that the meat was at the correct temp when it went out. We bbq our meat, bring it in and put it in a special warmer that keeps the bbq at 140 degrees. When an order comes up, it gets pulled out and cut on a sanitized cutting board, put in the correct box, and served to the customer. If anything drops below a certain temp, we flash it with fire to get it correct and put it back in the warmer immediately. Since he was new he was having a hard time with this procedure, but I have since set him straight and this issue should not arise again. As for the seasoning, I have never heard anyone say this. If anything I have heard that we add too much of our seasoning for some people. If we dropped the ball on that I apologize.\n\nAs for the ribs, we had no choice. True BBQ joints have to cook these items for hours and hours and we have to estimate how much we will need for the day. We DID have enough ribs to easily last us until 7, until someone came through and bought 7 racks and cleared us out near the end of the day. This happens sometimes and BBQ is first come first serve and I will not apologize for that. You are welcome to pre order any item that you want and we will cook extra and hold it for you.\n\nFlies are something that we just have to deal with in the valley, every business, especially outside joints like ours, has the same problem. The rains and then following heat in the surrounding pastures is causing this influx of flies and we are trying everything that we can to keep them at bay, but obviously it is a losing battle. I'm sorry this displeased you, trust me I know the feeling and spend hundreds trying to help with this, but it really is out of our control. Please don't hold us responsible for nature.\n\nIf you ever get the chance to come back through, please stop by, I would love to make it up to you with the order that you deserved to get!  Matthew Otten, Co-Owner"}< /Resp>

<Rating>3< /Rating>< text>
The food was mostly good, especially the mac and cheese side. But the prices are kinda high. For me: $19 for a sandwich and two sides after tax, no drink. While it was a pleasant day when I was there, the only seating is three picnic tables outside with umbrellas, right next to the highway, in the wind. Also parking consists of a driveway that will fit maybe 6 cars, but only two wide, so you could get stuck/have to get up in the middle of your meal to move for someone else. Or just order to go, but then your food is cold by the time you eat it.

Overall, they have good food, and I'd put up with the other inconveniences if they're prices were just lower. Unless your being served at a really nice restaurant, a bbq sandwich and sides should never be more than $12. And that should really include a drink.<//text>

< review>
My husband and I have been coming here shortly after they opened.  I absolutely LOVE the ribs.  Before Coppertop, I really didn't care for ribs.  I am sold!!   We visit Coppertop at least 7-10 times a year.
In a hurry to get to your destination?  They sell their food sealed in food-saver bags so you can heat and eat at home.  If you follow their hearing instructions it will taste as though it came right of the grill!  I always have minimum 1 rack in my freezer!
Today we figured they would be busy so I ordered/paid online for the first time.  What a time saver.  Just walk up to the side window to get your food and bypass the line at the order window.  I will be doing that again for sure!  I can't wait for Coppertop to ship their ribs which I understand is in the works.
Love this place!!!<//review>

<date>1429804845756</date><Gmap_id>0x80be49e5a0a9d64b:0xb4d2795461a540fa<//Gmap_id>< Name>
Stephanie Han< /Name>
<resp>{'time': 1444748033451, 'text': 'I love that the atmosphere was so nice when you visited, Stephanie. It\'s true that we\'re always hard at work here, but as you said, when that work results in our customers "sitting outdoors at a picnic table with some great BBQ," we\'d never complain! While I wish the tri-tip and ribs had been able to knock your socks off, I\'m glad you thought the pork was inching toward perfection. I hope you give us another chance to wow you even more soon! -Matthew Otten, Co-Owner'}< /resp>< userid>
105922283318214063748<//userid>
<review>Been wanting to try this place for a while, what with its top ranking in that Yelp list, and got my chance on the way home from Mammoth. My go-to BBQ spot had always been Holy Smoke BBQ in Bishop and I wanted to see how this place compared. First of all, there is no indoor seating so best for warmer weather days. Second, their menu is a little more limited than Holy Smoke but had the requisite basics so my friend and I decided to split a sampler platter. It came with brisket, bbq chicken, and baby back ribs, and I chose cole slaw and potato salad as my sides. The service here is very friendly and nice, and the owner was out watering the little patch of grass out front--a very lively and engaging person who talked to his patrons and took pictures, etc. It was a very jovial atmosphere and we couldn't have asked for nicer weather that day. Sitting outdoors at a picnic table with some great BBQ--what could be better?

Overall, I'd have to say I thought their food was very tasty, especially their chicken and pulled pork, which were damn near perfect, and I loved their sides, but there were a few small things that I wasn't completely thrilled with:

- their tri-tip was a little on the tough side
- some of the baby back ribs had their ends burnt a bit too much
- their BBQ sauce was a little too much on the sweet side and there were no other options

I'm no BBQ expert by any means but I was expecting to have my socks blown off and it just didn't happen. It was definitely worth a stop though, and I wholeheartedly wish them continued success because they are so nice and work very hard.< /review>< Rate>

< gmapID>
0x80be49e5a0a9d64b:0xb4d2795461a540fa</gmapID>
<Rating>5</Rating><Name>Forrest Sheldon</Name>< pics>
None< /pics>
< Time>
1458137038157<//Time>
< text>
The best ribs I've ever had.  We stopped in on the way back from Bishop having been chased out of climbing by rain.  I ordered the TriTip and my roommate ordered the pulled pork (us being North Carolina bbq fans).  While we waited, the owner came up and introduced himself and started showing us around their operation.  The ribs are brought in from VA and are the fattest set of ribs I've ever seen.  When we told him our order, he brought out a sample of the ribs to round it out.

The sandwiches were served on a  pressed pretzel bun and excellent.  The Tritip excellent and the pulled pork was quite good (better than anything else I've found in CA), but being an eastern NC bbq fan (vinegar sauce) I'm heavily biased against the inclusion of tomato.  That said, the thing to get is the ribs.  Tender smoky fatty goodness I haven't stopped thinking about them since.  Looking forward to getting back the next time we get a rainy day in Bishop.</text>
</record>
</dataset><record>

<userid>105288145658938251409< /userid><Name>Forrest Sheldon</Name>< Date>
1458137038157<//Date>
<rate>5<//rate>< review>
The best ribs I've ever had.  We stopped in on the way back from Bishop having been chased out of climbing by rain.  I ordered the TriTip and my roommate ordered the pulled pork (us being North Carolina bbq fans).  While we waited, the owner came up and introduced himself and started showing us around their operation.  The ribs are brought in from VA and are the fattest set of ribs I've ever seen.  When we told him our order, he brought out a sample of the ribs to round it out.

The sandwiches were served on a  pressed pretzel bun and excellent.  The Tritip excellent and the pulled pork was quite good (better than anything else I've found in CA), but being an eastern NC bbq fan (vinegar sauce) I'm heavily biased against the inclusion of tomato.  That said, the thing to get is the ribs.  Tender smoky fatty goodness I haven't stopped thinking about them since.  Looking forward to getting back the next time we get a rainy day in Bishop.<//review>

<UserId.>105692744256480109238</UserId.><user_name>Chelsea Madren (OC Food Diva)< /user_name>< Time>
1459991788990<//Time>
< Rate>
5< /Rate>
< review>
Big Pine Sampler Platter ($17.38) includes 5 ounces of Santa Maria tri-tip, two pork ribs, a quarter chicken, and a Hawaiian roll. These are all cooked out front in the smoker and grills so you know what you are getting. The tri-tip is cooked Santa Maria-style and seasoned with Hank‚Äôs own dry rub. The meat is juicy and full of savory beefy flavor that will have you coming back for more. The pork ribs are BBQ competition worthy with a good bite where it is tender but doesn‚Äôt just drop off the bone. The flavor has a good balance of smoky, sweet, and savory flavors. The chicken, whether you order white or dark, is moist and tender. The skin has the perfect caramelization with dark golden brown color. You can also taste the freshness of the chicken as it doesn‚Äôt have any irony flavor notes at all. The meat is almost sweet and the smoke imparts a great flavor throughout. Rating: 5/5

What is BBQ without sides? Fire Roasted Green Chili with Beans ($3.66 - 8 oz., $7.32 ‚Äì 16 oz., $13.73 ‚Äì 32 oz.) is a different take from the sweet barbeque beans usually served with BBQ. These are some of the best beans you‚Äôll ever eat! The savory flavor with green chile pepper tones works well with the black and chili beans. The flavor pairs well with the BBQ whether you have tri-tip, chicken, or pork ribs. If you have any tri-tip and beans leftover, cut up the tri-tip into small pieces and mix them up with the beans when you warm them up. It‚Äôs amazing like hearty, chunky chili. Rating: 5/5

Potato Salad ($3.66 - 8 oz., $7.32 ‚Äì 16 oz., $13.73 ‚Äì 32 oz.) is not your ordinary picnic salad. The potatoes are cooked just right, not hard and not mushy. The seasoning and mustard are balanced - the mustard flavor does not overpower it. The pickles and olives add just the right amount of salt and acidity. The presentation is very colorful as well. Rating: 4.8/5<//review>
<pictures>None<//pictures>< resp>
{'time': 1460133659373, 'text': "Thanks for the review, Chelsea -- I'm blown away by the thoroughness of your description! In particular, it's great to hear that the ribs seemed competition worthy! I hope you'll make it back our way for another good meal soon. -Matthew Otten, Co-Owner"}</resp>

<Review>Small portion too many flies toilets in the kitchen not very hygienic< /Review><pics>None< /pics>< Response>
{'time': 1563749490229, 'text': "Hi there! Thank you for your feedback. Portion size isn't really something that we get complaints on, in fact many people think we give out more food than they can eat so obviously I was surprised to see this. It is possible one of my cutters made a mistake and didn't fill up your portion enough, please let us know next time so we can address the issue. We would be happy to resolve any problems that you have while you are here! As for the flies, I'm sorry but blaming us for that is directing your frustration at people that are suffering from the same problem that you did. We pay hundreds a month for fly traps that we hang in the back, fly strips up around and inside the building, and I even pay a teenager to go around with a fly killing salt shotgun to keep them away from the customers. Unfortunately, LADWP waters the cow pastures around the town to keep the dust down, but it ends up making TONS of flies that we have to battle during the summer. We are doing everything we can but it's just completely out of our control. Lastly, the bathroom. Before we opened we asked the health inspector about the bathroom being in the main building and they said that there is plenty of space from the bathroom to the food area and that it isn't a concern. Not only that, we rent this building and the landlord refused to put in an outside bathroom. To remedy this, we have bought a different building down the road here in Big Pine and will be switching locations to that next year. Thank you again for you feedback, and I hope you will reconsider your rating on things that are out of our control. Hope to see you again!\nMatthew Kerley-Otten, Co-Owner"}<//Response>

< user_id>
115056594230180645639< /user_id>
<user_name>Michael Barnard< /user_name><Date>1372011799983</Date>< rating>
4<//rating>
< Text>
We stopped by on our way home from June Lake. Wow!  Great food! We had a pulled pork sandwich, tri tip sandwich, and a side of macaroni salad.  The pulled pork was delish!  It was a nice portion of meat on a soft roll.  Not too big, but plenty for me.  It was meat and bread. Nothing fancy or anything to distract from the top quality bbq.  I had the tri-tip sandwich.  The flavor of the tri-tip was excellent.  This is true BBQ - not just meat that was grilled outside. We shared a side of macaroni and cheese.  Again, the real McCoy - not some mix.  Thick macaroni noodles with gooey cheese.  The service was great, they had only been open a few days so they were still trying to work out some kinks, but they were friendly, up-beat, and checked back to make sure everything was okay.  Excellent for an place that only has counter service and outdoor picnic tables.< /Text>

Death Valley soda is sweet (American food) is also super creamy, and there are also vending machines that can buy self-heated meat, drinks and seasonings.
Cons:they tried to keep fly in control,but still like 3~ 4 flies bothers you while you dine. and the cooling water just too powerful that will sprayed on your face and food,and the red tent make the food less delicious looking.
Disadvantages: Although they have tried to control the number of flies, there are still about three or four flies trying to split the cup. The cooling spray is too thick, the wind is full of food, and the red tent is transparent. Light causes food to look bad

< Review>
(Translated by Google) Barbecue lovers, we were thrilled to come and test this place having been decreed "best barbecue of the US" qql years ago. Bah thin, if this is the best barbecue in the country ...
OK, that's ok, but we were really disappointed with the reviews of this restaurant. We had two meals "Santa Maria tri-tip" and a "pulled pork". The pulled pork was very tender, but it is cooked in a sauce, so you do not smell the "smoked" barbecue.
When to the beef, what a disappointment! A little tender, but it's a thick piece, so that the interior is cooked, the interior is burned. No taste of smoke there either, just burned on a meat a little doubtful. Great.
I do not put less than three stars as it was when mm OK, the large quantities and the correct prices. Maybe the restaurant is typical of American BBQ, I do not know, but we were disappointed.
So love barbecues, do not plan to stop there along the way with envy like us!

(Translated by Google) Barbecue lovers, we were thrilled to come and test this place having been decreed "best barbecue of the US" qql years ago. Bah thin, if this is the best barbecue in the country ...
OK, that's ok, but we were really disappointed with the reviews of this restaurant. We had two meals "Santa Maria tri-tip" and a "pulled pork". The pulled pork was very tender, but it is cooked in a sauce, so you do not smell the "smoked" barbecue.
When to the beef, what a disappointment! A little tender, but it's a thick piece, so that the interior is cooked, the interior is burned. No taste of smoke there either, just burned on a meat a little doubtful. Great.
I do not put less than three stars as it was when mm OK, the large quantities and the correct prices. Maybe the restaurant is typical of American BBQ, I do not know, but we were disappointed.
So love barbecues, do not plan to stop there along the way with envy like us!
